<paragraph id="7F4736F74F22FFF7F0FAF8A8FC8A6F78" blockId="15.[240,799,1827,1884]" box="[240,799,1859,1884]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
Refer to 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F22FFF7F15EF8A8FE696F7F" author="Engel, M. S." box="[340,508,1859,1883]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="165 - 196" refId="ref12309" refString="Engel, M. S. 1999 a. The taxonomy of recent and fossil honey bees (Hymenoptera: Apidae; Apis). Journal of Hymenoptera Research 8: 165 - 196." type="journal article" year="1999">Engel (1999a)</bibRefCitation>
for complete synonymy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="37E2657C4F3DFFE8F0CAFF28FC2D691F" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph id="7F4736F74F3DFFE8F0CAFF28FAE768FF" blockId="16.[192,1440,195,315]" box="[192,1394,195,219]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F3DFFE8F0CAFF28FF6668FF" bold="true" box="[192,243,195,219]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">GD:</emphasis>
Cosmopolitan; present on most or all of the islands of Greater 
<collectingCountry id="07EF76674F3DFFE8F3E9FF2FFBE668FF" box="[995,1139,195,219]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
, except Mona Island.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F4736F74F3DFFE8F0FAFF08FC2D691F" blockId="16.[192,1440,195,315]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">
The domestic honey bee, introduced from Europe by colonists in the 17 
<superScript id="888D9BBF4F3DFFE8F44EFF09FBC668D4" attach="left" box="[1092,1107,226,240]" fontSize="6" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">th</superScript>
century (
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F3DFFE8F4CCFF08FAF468DF" author="Engel, M. S." box="[1222,1377,227,251]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" pagination="165 - 196" refId="ref12309" refString="Engel, M. S. 1999 a. The taxonomy of recent and fossil honey bees (Hymenoptera: Apidae; Apis). Journal of Hymenoptera Research 8: 165 - 196." type="journal article" year="1999">Engel 1999a</bibRefCitation>
), has colonized 
<collectingCountry id="07EF76674F3DFFE8F133FEEFFE5D693F" box="[313,456,259,283]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
for a long time. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F3DFFE8F327FEE8FC58693F" author="Ledru, A. P." box="[813,973,259,283]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" refId="ref14025" refString="Ledru, A. P. 1863. Viage a la isla de Puerto Rico en el ano 1797, ejecutado por una comision de sabios franceses, de orden de su gobierno y bajo la direccion del capitan N. Baudin, con objeto de hacer indagaciones y colecciones relativas a la historia natural … Imprenta Militar de J. Gonzalez; Puerto Rico. 265 p." type="book" year="1863">Ledru (1863)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F3DFFE8F402FEE8FB4D693F" author="Gundlach, J." box="[1032,1240,259,283]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" pagination="115 - 199" refId="ref13374" refString="Gundlach, J. 1887. Apuntes para la fauna Puerto-riquena. Sexta parte. Anales de la Sociedad Espanola de Historia Natural 15: 115 - 199." type="journal article" year="1887">Gundlach (1887)</bibRefCitation>
, the species was already well established in the island’s non-cultivated habitats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
